1.  I faced issue when connecting backend container to mongodb container,
the error says  ---> MongooseServerSelectionError: connect ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:27017
127.0.0.1 (or localhost) inside a Docker container refers to that container itself, not your Windows machine and not the MongoDB container.

So your backend is trying to connect to MongoDB running inside the backend container, but there is no MongoDB server there.
need to change server.js file here, ===> that is from mongoose.connect("mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/<db name>");  to ====> "mongodb://<mongodb-container-name>:27017/<db name>"


